article.description: — Abou Ousmane had 19 points in North Texas' 75-45 win against Omaha on Saturday night.
article.headline: North Texas earns 75-45 win against Omaha
article.linkText: North Texas earns 75-45 win against Omaha
article.story: DENTON, Texas -- — Abou Ousmane had 19 points in North Texas' 75-45 win against Omaha on Saturday night. Ousmane also contributed eight rebounds for the Mean Green (6-2). Jayden Martinez added 13 points while shooting 4 for 9, including 4 for 4 from beyond the arc, and he also had six rebounds. Aaron Scott shot 4 of 6 from the field and 3 for 4 from the line to finish with 11 points. Frankie Fidler finished with 14 points and two blocks for the Mavericks (3-6). Akol Arop added 12 points for Omaha. In addition, JJ White finished with six points and four steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
